Turkey Will Focus on Health, Job-Creation in 2012 Budget

-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c
-- 
2011-10-18T07:48:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/turkey-will-focus-on-health-job-creation-in-2012-budget.html
Turkey ’s government will spend money
on the health system and creating jobs in next year’s budget,
Finance Minister Mehmet Simsek said.  Job creation  will be encouraged by reducing the payroll
burden, backed with 5.5 billion liras of funding, Simsek said at
a news conference in Ankara today. Health spending will rise
10.1 percent next year, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Berat Meric in Ankara at 
 americ@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
